cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about sequence-to-sequence modeling, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses deep neural language modeling, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper introduces a new training scheme that improves the performance of seq2seq models, which could be considered an advancement in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of beam search, which is a common optimization technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on tasks such as machine translation, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV).
